title: University of Utah Collegiate race
description: This is a collegiate race hosted by the University of Utah.  On Saturday morning we will be holding a road race that is on a flat five mile circuit with 1.75 miles of dirt/gravel road.  On Saturday evening we will be holding a time trail.  On Sunday morning we will be holding a criterium.  Due to unexpected road construction we are still finalizing the location of the time trail and criterium.
course: For the road race on Saturday morning it will be a flat five mile circuirt with 1.75 miles of dirt/gravel road.  It is loacted between 2100 N. to 3300 N. and 2200 W to 3200 W.
registration: For the road race on Saturday morning riders can registor using Sportsbaseonline, or they can pay the morning of the race.
directions: The course is located in Salt Lake City between 2100 N. to 3300 N. and 2200 W to 3200 W. Take I-215 exit #25 go west and at the first intersection (2100 N.) turn right (north) on 2200 W. Located approximately 1/2 mile down the road on the east side is a softball park that will be used for parking, registration, awards, and port-o-lets.
